@jack If “the application” is “Instabase”, then
• Programming languages: Java, Python, Go, Typescript
• Third party frameworks or APIs: In terms of big “frameworks”, we use React in the frontend, Flask at the API layer, Redis+RabbitMQ+Celery in the distributed system backend, GRPC and Thrift for cross-service communication. If “APIs” just mean any 3rd party APIs that we use, there’s a ton — are we looking to list out all 3rd party libs used by Instabase?
